FBIS3-23496 "jptot013__l94024" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 24 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA MEXICO `Pacifist' Writer Arrested for Killing Candidate Colosio Initial Confirmed Report PA2403022794 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 0145 GMT 24 Mar 94 PA2403022794 Mexico City XEW Television Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [See Selected Video Reports section for worldwide TV coverage of killing] [Excerpt] We have Ubaldo Diaz of the newspaper OVACIONES, from Tijuana. Go ahead Ubaldo. Diaz: This afternoon at 1908 Luis Donaldo Colosio, presidential candidate for the ruling Institutional Revolutionary Party [PRI], was the target of an attack. He apparently sustained two bullet wounds -- one in the head and one in the chest. The political rally was being held in the Lomas de Tijuana neighborhood, better known as Lomas Taurinas. Colosio was leading a political rally here for 3,000 persons. At the end of the rally, as he was leaving the podium, two individuals, a young person and an older one, approached him with pistols and managed to shoot the PRI candidate. [passage omitted]
